<a name="Question Management">
<h3>
2.3. Question Management
</h3>
</a>

<p>
This introductory scenario shows an individual user creating and editing questions.
Question management is one of the key functionalities of the Test Tool. This section
deals with the management of questions within tests. To see how the user gets here, refer to
<a href="test-creation.html">
Section 2.2
</a>

<p>
When the user adds a new question and chooses <tt>New Question</tt>, the following screen will 
appear.

<br>
<hr>
<a name="Adding a New Question">
<p align=center>
<img src="images/add-new-question.png">
</p>
<p align=center> Figure 3-1: Adding a New Question </p>
<hr>
</a>
<br>

<p>
To the right of every question, there is a red button with a white minus button on it. The user
clicks this button to delete the question.
<p>
The user first chooses the desired question type using the drop-down menu as shown in 
Figure 3-2.

<br>
<hr>
<a name="Question Type Selection">
<p align=center>
<img src="images/question-type-selection.png">
</p>
<p align=center> Figure 3-2: Question Type Selection </p>
<hr>
</a>
<br>

<p>
Once the user chooses a question type, the system will adjust the screen accordingly to 
display the different sections needed to create a question of that type. These different 
question types are shown in this section's subsections.

<p>
Once a question type is selected, a blue/yellow save button will also appear next to the red delete button. 
Clicking this will allow the user to the save the question to the Question Bank. The save button is shown in Figure 3-3.

<br>
<hr>
<a name="Question Type Selection">
<p align=center>
<img src="images/save.png">
</p>
<p align=center> Figure 3-3: Save Button </p>
<hr>
</a>
<br>

<p>
The common sections found across multiple question types are <tt>Question</tt>, <tt>Points</tt>, 
<tt>Subject</tt>, and <tt>Difficulty</tt>.

<p> 
<tt>Question</tt> and <tt>Points</tt> require the user to type in information using the keyboard.
There are show in Figure 3-4 and 3-5, respectively.
<br>*note* The <tt>Points</tt> section only accepts numbers. 

<br>
<hr>
<a name="Question Type Selection">
<p align=center>
<img src="images/question.png">
</p>
<p align=center> Figure 3-4: Question Box </p>
<hr>
</a>
<br>

<br>
<hr>
<a name="Question Type Selection">
<p align=center>
<img src="images/points.png">
</p>
<p align=center> Figure 3-5: Points Box </p>
<hr>
</a>
<br>

<p> 
<tt>Subject</tt>, <tt>Difficulty</tt>, and <tt>Course</tt> acquire info through drop-down menus similar to the 
<tt>Type</tt> section. <tt>Subject</tt> is chosen from a list of subjects that the user creates. The user can click <tt>Add</tt> 
to add a new subject to the list. <tt>Difficulty</tt> is chosen from a list ranging from 1 - 10. And <tt>Course</tt> is chosen 
from a list of courses that the user creates. The user can click <tt>Add</tt> to add a new course to the list. These are shown in Figures 3-6, 
3-7, and 3-8 respectively.

